Sentences are withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four (4) years.    Conditions of probation are:
1) Maintain full-time employment/job search combination;
2) AODA assessment and follow through counseling; 
3) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
5) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
6) Use only one doctor and only one pharmacist unless approved by agent;
7) Reimburse Metro Drug $250.00 buy money; 
8) Pay costs of action; 
9) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
10) On count 3, spend eleven (11) months in jail, under the Huber Law including child care, to commence on 02-03-17 at 5:00 p.m.  
11) Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge.   
Defendant is entitled to 24 days credit should probation be revoked.   
